pted to sharp and sudden changes in the international system during the twentieth century, this book offers essential insights for those who hope to navigate toward peace across today’s altered and uncertain strategic landscape.Contributors to this volume:Carole Fink, Gregory Flynn, William I. Hitchcock, Michael Howard, Paul Kennedy, Diane B. Kunz, Melvyn P. Leffler, Charles S. Maier, Tony Smith, Marc Trachtenberg, Randall B. Woods, Philip Zelikow  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNationalismxHistoryy20th century. 0aRacismxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld politicsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh1 aFink, Carole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlynn, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHitchcock, William I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoward, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKunz, Diane B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeffler, Melvyn P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaier, Charles S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrachtenberg, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoods, Randall B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZelikow, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014748340uhttps://www.degruyter.com